Around 314,000 people lost their jobs in the three months prior to September in the UK, with hospitality, retailing and leisure amongst the hardest hit industries. As the Arcadia retail group, which owns brands including Topshop and Dorothy Perkins, goes into administration and Debenhams looks set to close for good, we’d like to hear from retailer workers who have lost their job as a result of the coronavirus pandemic. You can get in touch by filling in the form below. Your responses are secure as the form is encrypted and only the Guardian has access to your contributions. One of our journalists will be in contact before we publish, so please do leave contact details. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.